ticket.subject: Datorama Salesforce Integration For Pacing
ticket.note:
I will reach out to Gary regarding the definitions for the possible Unit types:
1. CPM 2. VIEW 3. EACH 4. PCT 5. Value Added 6. CPC 7. SUB
Also reaching out to Dave for Andrew's second question.

From Gary,
1. CPM - Cost per one thousand impressions. Ex - 500,000 display impressions at a $9 "CPM" = $4,500 in total spend. Used for display ads, mobile ads, video ads, retargeting, and addressable TV. 2. VIEW - Cost per single "view" of a video ad. This is rarely used as we typically price video on a CPM basis as well. Actually, it doesn't look like we have any active products that use this model at the moment. 3. EACH - Cost per one unit. This is a general pricing model and can be used for anything from creative (price per one banner ad) to match fees (price per one data match), or a campaign management fee. This is more of a catch-all pricing model. 4. PCT - Used when a product is marked up by a specific percentage. Ex - Facebook is typically marked up by 20% or so. Paid search is also marked up by a percentage. 5. Value Added - Used when we throw in additional impressions for free. If clients ask, I'll typically throw in an additional 10% of their paid impression total for free. These are called "Value-Added" impressions. 6. CPC - Cost per click. This is exactly what it sounds like. Similar to "VIEW", this pricing model is not used often. Looks like we only offer this for high impact ads. 7. SUB - I didn't know this one, so I looked it up under products in SF. Looks like this is price per additional subscriber. The products using this are all YouTube ads, so it must be price per additional YouTube subscriber.

ticket.note: SELECT DISTINCT z.CAMPAIGN_IO as 'ACTIVE_CAMPAIGN_IO' , s.IO as 'SF_CLOSED_CAMPS' FROM ( SELECT DISTINCT aap.IO as 'CAMPAIGN_IO' ,'ADWORDS' as 'PLATFORM' FROM ap.adwords_adgroup_performance_day aap WHERE aap.date BETWEEN CURDATE() AND DATE_SUB(CURDATE(),INTERVAL 6 MONTH) UNION SELECT DISTINCT aia.insertion_order_id as 'CAMPAIGN_IO' ,'APPNEXUS' as 'PLATFORM' FROM ap.appnexus_impressions_activity aia WHERE aia.date BETWEEN CURDATE() AND DATE_SUB(CURDATE(),INTERVAL 6 MONTH) UNION SELECT DISTINCT da.IO as 'CAMPAIGN_IO' ,'DBM' as 'PLATFORM' FROM ap.dbm_impressions_activity da WHERE da.Date BETWEEN CURDATE() AND DATE_SUB(CURDATE(),INTERVAL 6 MONTH) UNION SELECT DISTINCT dia.IO as 'CAMPAIGN_IO' ,'DFA' as 'PLATFORM' FROM ap.dfa_impressions_activity dia WHERE dia.Date BETWEEN CURDATE() AND DATE_SUB(CURDATE(),INTERVAL 6 MONTH) AND dia.Site <> 'Turn' UNION SELECT DISTINCT fai.IO as 'CAMPAIGN_IO' ,'FACEBOOK' as 'PLATFORM' FROM ap.facebook_ad_impressions fai WHERE fai.Date BETWEEN CURDATE() AND DATE_SUB(CURDATE(),INTERVAL 6 MONTH) UNION SELECT DISTINCT ti.IO as 'CAMPAIGN_IO' ,'TRADEDESK' as 'PLATFORM' FROM ap.tradedesk_impressions ti WHERE ti.Date BETWEEN CURDATE() AND DATE_SUB(CURDATE(),INTERVAL 6 MONTH) UNION SELECT DISTINCT tia.IO as 'CAMPAIGN_IO' ,'TURN' as 'PLATFORM' FROM ap.turn_impressions_activity tia WHERE tia.date BETWEEN CURDATE() AND DATE_SUB(CURDATE(),INTERVAL 6 MONTH) ) z JOIN salesforce.salesforce_all_list s ON z.CAMPAIGN_IO = s.IO WHERE YEAR(s.End_Date) < 2017;

Proper query is:
SELECT DISTINCT dia.IO ,dia.Campaign ,dia.Date ,s.End_Date ,s.Digital_Strategist FROM ap.dfa_impressions_activity dia JOIN salesforce.salesforce_all_list s ON dia.IO = s.IO WHERE dia.Date = '2017-06-19' AND s.End_Date <> '2017-06-19' AND s.End_Date IS NOT NULL AND s.End_Date < '2017-06-19' AND dia.IO <> '';
